race.comment: HENRY'S BLADE (2) loves it here around the Rocky circuit with a win and two seconds from just four spins and will be ready to peak now third run back from the break. Handles all going and should be right there when the whips are cracking. KAI MONDO (3) saves his best form for his home track here and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Expected to be in the finish. KING SPIRIT (4) got a well-deserved victory here at the latest outing and winning rider Tierney sticks. Again gets the benefit of her 3kg claim and is a must for the exotics players. OUR TURN NOW (7) is a bit hit or miss but is more than capable enough on his day. Among the main hopes if he brings his A-game. NICCONORI (9) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be underestimated.
